Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with Valeo. I bring over three years of professional experience in software development, AI systems, and research, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade software systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an AI interaction layer translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous software architecture design, API contract development, and SDK patterns to enable automated customer actions. I designed software architectures and frameworks for generative code solutions, accelerating developer integration through structured templates and validation workflows. To ensure production readiness, I built an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to debug failures and track quality — skills that translate directly to prototyping and testing new use cases in automotive driving assistance and immersive communications. I also engineered a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, enabling scalable tool execution across complex workflows with cross-functional integration points. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions following agile development process. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to developing innovative software solutions, frameworks, and APIs that advance Valeo's mission to make mobility safer, smarter and more sustainable.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in emerging technologies, validation testing, and technical mentorship — skills that align directly with the innovation and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate fashion designs using CUDA, PyTorch and LORA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. I was responsible for developing validation tests and evaluation metrics to determine if model outputs met project goals — directly mirroring the responsibility to lead the design of validation tests for software outputs in this role. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students, mentoring participants on emerging technologies. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who researches emerging technologies, brainstorms innovative user experiences, and communicates with clarity, all of which I would bring to Valeo's innovation projects.

I have always been passionate about innovation in automotive solutions and sustainability, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Valeo's mission to make mobility safer, smarter and more sustainable. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

